Part 1: Basic File & Directory Management
These are daily-use commands for any Linux Admin.
Copy code

pwd            # Present working directory
ls -l          # List files with details
ls -a          # Show hidden files
cd /path       # Change directory
mkdir dir1     # Create directory
rmdir dir1     # Remove empty directory
rm -rf dir1    # Remove directory forcefully
cp file1 file2 # Copy file
mv file1 file2 # Move/Rename file
touch file.txt # Create empty file
cat file.txt   # View file content
less file.txt  # View large file
head -n 10 file.txt
tail -n 10 file.txt
